reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 13, 2022
reviews.reviewText: If you're looking for a small shelf with enough space for various things, this is perfect. I was able to not only have a place to put my crafts, candles, and books, but it doesn't take up a lot of space. The drawers are great for lose items and it was very easy to assemble.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small but gorgeous
reviews.reviewText: This looks even better in person. Excellent quality and a gorgeous piece. Easy to assemble. My only criticism is that it is smaller than I had anticipated but I still love and recommend it

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 4, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars No instructions but still not bad.
reviews.reviewText: So the reason for the four star is because it didn't come with instructions to install it. I straight had to wind it and it took a lot longer than if I had a diagram or something. Basically I looked at the picture on Amazon to figure out where pieces went.It did come with extra screws which is nice if you know where you are putting them.All in all it was easy enough to build...from the bottom up is how I did it. Not saying all packages will come without instructions just saying mine didn't.It is a bit smaller than I thought but thats what you get when not looking at the dimensions before buying...my bad so it doesn't effect the review at all.It is Hella sturdy though...not like those Walmart cheap bookshelves. This one I could do a balancing act with my husband on top and I know it would hold.The drawers are your basic fabric and look kinda cheap but when they are in it doesn't look bad. I may paint them with fabric paint later to make them black instead of the weird brown shade they are.For the most part I am happy and would buy this again. Everything was nicely wrapped so it wouldn't get scratches are damaged in the shipping.I am not sure if the price is worth it since I'm a cheap person, however I didn't break the bank to horrible for the piece.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 18, 2022

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not as big as pictures looked
reviews.reviewText: I got my self today when ups dropped I’d noticed it wasn’t in as big as package as expected and was think ok maybe it’s just a lot of parts. No biggie. Pictures are very deceiving. Even the ones other people took this self looked a LOT bigger. My 5 year old is taller then this thing so wasn’t to impressed with that and the cubbies are very small I was at least expecting regular size cubes. But they are the really small ones. The Assembly was fast with a screw gun. Wasn’t really looking for this small of a shelf but I have it and I guess I’ll make it work somewhere just not where or what I needed it for. Lesson learned, Don’t go off pictures
